<p>I am using a couple of <code>Button</code> controls in a <code>ColumnLayout</code>, and an inline <code>Component</code> to define the <code>ButtonStyle</code> for each button. </p>  <p>I would like the size of the <code>Button</code>s to be relative to the text size of the label in the <code>ButtonStyle</code>.   </p>  <p>However I have no idea how to refer externally to the <code>width</code> or <code>height</code> fields of the <code>Text</code> component within <code>ButtonStyle</code>, or whether this can even be done?</p>  <p>See the code below:</p>  <pre><code>import QtQuick.Window 2.2 import QtQuick.Controls 1.3 import QtQuick.Controls.Styles 1.3 import QtQuick.Layouts 1.1  Rectangle {   height: 200   width: 200   color: "white"   border.color: "black"    ColumnLayout {       spacing: 4        Component {           id: filterButtonStyle           ButtonStyle {               label: Text {                   font.pixelSize: 11                   text: control.text                   verticalAlignment: Text.AlignVCenter                   horizontalAlignment: Text.AlignHCenter               }           }       }        Button {           id: testButton1           width: 30           height: 20           text: "Test 1"           style: filterButtonStyle       }        Button {           id: testButton2           width: 30           height: 20           text: "Test 2"           style: filterButtonStyle       }    } }  </code></pre>